CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1782051073
OL,3,CMan denies knowing age of alleged
OL,4,Cvictim in Rhyl child exploitation trial
OL,6,FMr Singh told the court that he had
OL,7,Fvisited a pet store in Rhyl with two
OL,8,Fof the teenage girls at the centre of
OL,9,Fthis case - Child B and Child C - when
OL,10,Fthe subject of visiting London came up.
OL,12,FHe said that whilst he was prepared to
OL,13,Ftake Child B, who he claimed to
OL,14,Fbelieve was 17 at the time of the
OL,15,Fvisit to London, he refused Child C
OL,16,Fsaying: ''I'm sorry but you can't come
OL,17,Fbecause you are 15.''
OL,19,FDuncan Bould, his defence counsel
OL,20,Freplied: ''So what was the distinction
OL,21,Fbetween the two of them?''
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/6
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,434,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1782051073
OL,3,CMan denies knowing age of alleged
OL,4,Cvictim in Rhyl child exploitation trial
OL,6,FMr Singh answered: "The age."
OL,8,FDuncan Bould added: "So you know later
OL,9,Fon that she was 15.....what would your
OL,10,Freaction have been in that case?'
OL,12,FMr Singh said: "I wouldn't have taken
OL,13,Fher, no chance."
OL,15,F"Did it cross your mind she's 17. I
OL,16,Fneed to ask her parents or guardians
OL,17,For whatever." Duncan Bould said.
OL,19,FMr Singh replied: "No, it's a silly
OL,20,Fmistake, but no."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/6
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
